What is html?
html stands for hypertext markup language.
html is used for create website webpages or webpage structure.
html first time release in 1986 bt Tim berner lee
html file extension save with  .html or .htm
html is not any language it is a markup langauge 


What is hypertext ?
hypertext means redirect one page to another page
ex: <a href="https://www.tops-int.com"> click to open tops</a>

WHat is markup language?
html is not any language it is a markup language.
markup language is html load on web browser or interact with browser so we called it is markup language.

html is case-insensitive markup language.
ex: <html> or <HTML> or <Html>

html provide tag and its defined inside of <> angular brackets.
html tag provide structure of webpage.
a) paired tag
b) non-paired tag

a) paired tag:
    paired tag define <p></p> which defines start and close this is called paired tag.
    ex: <h1></h1> or <p></p>

b) non paired tag
    non-paired tage defines <hr> start and not need to close this is called non-paired.
    ex: <hr> , <br> , <input> , <meta> , <link> , <img> and <p>

What is Boiler plate or html structure or html skeleton..?




